Key Match Events: The Rangers scored three runs in the first inning against Astros starter Cristian Javier.
Corey Seager homered with one out, and the next four batters reached against Javier, with two of them scoring.
The Astros cut the Rangers' lead to 4-2 with a Bregman homer in the third and chased Texas starter Max Scherzer after 2 2/3 innings.
The Rangers rocked J.P. France for four runs in the fourth to take an 8-2 lead, including a two-run single by Adolis García.
Nathaniel Lowe’s homer in the sixth made it 10-2.
Post-Match Reflections: Astros third baseman Alex Bregman said, 'Definitely not what you want,' referring to the loss.
Manager Dusty Baker appreciated the team's effort and told players he loved them and appreciated their professionalism.
Catcher Martín Maldonado reflected on the season's achievements despite the loss.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Astros lost 22 of their final 29 games at home, including the playoffs.
The series loss marked the end of the Astros' reign as champions after a successful run of seven seasons.
